Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with measuring network delay and estimating throughput metrics in TCP/IP networks. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also a possible category as the paper may discuss security implications of measuring network delay and estimating throughput metrics. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is another possible category as the paper may discuss the information-theoretic aspects of measuring network delay and estimating throughput metrics. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is a less likely category, but the paper may discuss the impact of network delay and throughput on multimedia applications. 
- cs.PF (Performance) is also a less likely category, but the paper may discuss the performance evaluation of the proposed method for estimating throughput metrics.
